Post._content:
Welcome to [Hexo](https://hexo.io/)! This is your very first post. Check [documentation](https://hexo.io/docs/) for more info. If you get any problems when using Hexo, you can find the answer in [troubleshooting](https://hexo.io/docs/troubleshooting.html) or you can ask me on [GitHub](https://github.com/hexojs/hexo/issues).

## Quick Start

### Create a new post

``` bash
$ hexo new "My New Post"
```

More info: [Writing](https://hexo.io/docs/writing.html)

### Run server

``` bash
$ hexo server
```

More info: [Server](https://hexo.io/docs/server.html)

### Generate static files

``` bash
$ hexo generate
```

More info: [Generating](https://hexo.io/docs/generating.html)

### Deploy to remote sites

``` bash
$ hexo deploy
```

More info: [Deployment](https://hexo.io/docs/deployment.html)

Post.title: JavaScript
Post.content:
ES6

Person

function Person(name, age){
    // 
    this.name = name;
    this.age = age;
    function privateName(){
    // constructorPerson1
        console.log("Name is: "+this.name);
        return this.name;
    };
    var privateAge = function(){
    // constructorPerson2
        console.log("Age is: "+this.age);
        return this.age;
    };
    this.publicFunc = function(){
        // thiscall
        privateName.call(this);  
        privateAge.call(this);
    }

};
var Peter = new Person("Peter", 24);
Peter.privateAge();  // undefined 
Peter.publicFunc();  // console will print name and age

######

  1. new
  2. prototype

Person (by Module Pattern)

var PersonMP = (function(name, age){
    this.name = name;
    this.age = age;
    function privateName(){
        return this.name;
    };
    function privateAge(){
        return this.age;
    }
    return {
        publicFunc : function(){
            privateName.call(this);
            privateAge.call(this);
        }
    }
})();

######

  1. public/private
  2. debug

retrunpublic methodAPIIIFE

  1. callscope

    //this
    _:function(fun){
    var that = this;
    return function(){

       return fun.apply(that,arguments); // return

    }
    }

    2.constructorModel PatternIIFEPerson.prototype

    function Person(name,age){
    this.name = name;
    this.age = age;
    }
    Person.prototype = (function(){
    function privateName(){

       return this.name;

    };
    function privateAge(){

       return this.age;

    }
    return {

       constructor : Person, // constructor prototype
   publicFunc : function(){
       this._(privateName);
       this._(privateAge);
   }
   _ : function(fun){
       var that = this;
       return function(){
           return fun.apply(that, arguments); // return
       }
   }

    })();

ES6

class

  1. // ES6
    // :
    class Person{
    static get name(){

    return 'jelly';

    }
    };
    Person.name; //


  2. //
    const TbFedMembers = (() => {
    const HuaChen = jelly;

    return class{
    getOneMemberName(){
    return HuaChen;
    }
    };
    })();
